==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}}.
At the top of the character is possibly a representation of a room at the centre of a corridor (compare {{zh-l|*良}}); at the bottom, there is a foot pointing down {{zh-l|*夊}}. The original meaning is "going back", with perhaps a reference to meet people such as in a guest room. Original version of {{zh-l|*復}}. Unrelated to {{zh-l|*夏}}.

The top component of the character is unrelated to {{zh-l|*每}}, {{zh-l|*傷}}, {{zh-l|*旅}}, {{zh-l|*乞}} as well as {{zh-l|*人}}.

